ced that mobs conned correctly now while sneaking/hiding, undead were considering indifferent, and small dogs where indiff unless they could see me.  Before the patch, all of the undead and small dogs considered scowling.  Nice upgrade in my opinion.<br>
<br>
<br>
Lagrius<br>
59th blackguard<br>
Terris Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucutelilia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CuteLilia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 1:42:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Did you happen to notice...</span><hr size=1> Yep yep. Very neat. Now...if I actually took the time and notice these things....=)<br>
<br>
Lil<br>
Terris Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udarthender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarthEnder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 1:44:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Did you happen to notice...</span><hr size=1> I noticed this from the goos in Dalnirs.<br>
<br>
If this is really like we think it is this is GREAT!<br>
<br>
Question is, do all mobs con indifferent while sneak/hiding now?  Or do the ones that see through it still con scowls? <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/dboulais_1999/Thief03.jpg">
<i><br>Keenedge
<br>Master Assassin of the Order of the Ebon Mask</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urohaise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rohaise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 2:48:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Did you happen to notice...</span><hr size=1> I spent time in both Karnor's and Howling Stones tonight.  Two places notorious for incorrect /cons.  I also ran through Skyfire and Overthere.<br>
<br>
It looks like both of these dungeons, as well as at least two other test areas, now give correct cons for not only hide/sneak, but invis as well.<br>
<br>
Karnors -  ALL undead now conned indifferent, they used to scowl though never see me.<br>
Karnors - Most small dogs conned indifferent, used to all scowl whether they saw me or not.  Some were were scowling, about 20%, and only those that scowled saw me.<br>
<br>
Howling Stones - Almost everything, including undead and biles now con indifferent, when they all used to scowl (and only rarely see me).  I found three biles, however, that scowled when others were indifferent.  I did not get close enough to check accuracy of the /con, but I would assume, based on previous experience, that those biles would have aggroed on me had I gotten close enough.<br>
<br>
Skyfire - Wurms/Mature wurms conned indifferent.  They used to scowl yet not see me.<br>
<br>
Overthere - Sabretooth conned indifferent to both rogue and druid when invis.  Used to scowl to both when invis (I think, not positive on that one).<br>
<br>
Summary: looks like they fixed the /con for factionless mobs when invis, and not just for rogues.<br>
<br>
Downside to this:  Now I have to /con everything, whereas before I would just zip through real fast hoping it wouldn't see me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upatofnaud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>patofnaud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 9:00:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> To cool!</span><hr size=1> Anyone happen to con any Giants?? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urohaise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rohaise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 11:42:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To cool!</span><hr size=1> I passed through Frontier Mountains as well, conned a giant indifferentthere.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uechus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Echus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 11:59:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To cool!</span><hr size=1> Oh sure, it's really cool.  But I've spent the last 20 levelsbuilding up a database of creatures that saw through sneak/hide,at what level, and how they conned.  All that obsessive workwasted!  Wasted I tell you!<br>
<br>
Myabe my next project willbe to count the number of polygons in Warslik Woods.  I bet noone has done that yet.<br>
<br>
Echus Mordax<br>
49th rogue<br>
7th Hammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udarthender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarthEnder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 12:37:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To cool!</span><hr size=1> Wow.  This is really fantastic!<br>
<br>
Now only one more thingneeds to be changed as it applies to conning.<br>
<br>
Mobs thatnormally WOULD attack you, but don't because of your level, shouldnot con &quot;scowls at you, ready to attack&quot; or &quot;glaresat you threateningly&quot; because in reality, they are sittingthere cowering in fear hoping you decide to ignore them.<br>
<br>
I hate it when I decide NOT to sneak around a green dungeonand everything is scowling, but nothing is attacking, and thenout of no where one of the greens is like a level higher thanthe rest and decide to take a swing at me.<br>
<br>
This shouldonly apply to things that normally attack on site though, aspeople who are amiable, would still be amiable even if your muchmore powerful than them.<br>
<br>
The massage would read somethinglike:<br>
<br>
&quot;an orc pawn cringes away from you, too afraidto attack - it looks like a reasonable safe opponent&quot;<br>
<br>
But I'd make do with having them con apprehensive, as thatmakes sense for someone who hates you but is also too afraidto attack. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/dboulais_1999/Thief03.jpg">
<i><br>Keenedge
<br>Master Assassin of the Order of the Ebon Mask</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhyarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 1:02:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To cool!</span><hr size=1> Has anybody checked out the frogs in OS yet? <p><img src="http://rites.securix.net/~sylvan/sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urohaise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rohaise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 1:05:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To cool!</span><hr size=1> Frogs in OS always gave the correct con message.<br>
<br>
I'mguessing they are unchanged.<br>
<br>
The only thing changedthat I can see is that stuff that used to give incorrect consnow give a correct con.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukenric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kenric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 1:11:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Be careful though...</span><hr size=1> I can't remember who said it, some Admin somewheres (I thinkhere actually), but I think Kendrick said that there wouldn'tbe any changes to those &quot;incorrect&quot; cons...he saidsomething like we should be exploring which mobs can see andwhich mobs cannot regardless.  <br>
<br>
Just warning ya...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 2:37:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hoels76.tripod.com/wee.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Be careful though...</span><hr size=1> check guk<br>
icebones<br>
sol b<br>
bugs <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwolvinsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolvinsbane</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wlvrn.com/images/dag.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 3:10:46 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.wlvrn.com/images/bert.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Be careful though...</span><hr size=1> I got correct cons on Bugs in Sol B last night.  Bat also connedcorrectly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uenkara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Enkara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 4:46:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Be careful though...</span><hr size=1> I'll check in Sebilis tonight.<br>
<br>
I wonder if this willfinally allow me to know which shamans can see me and which onescan't.  If this is accurate it will be invaluable for corpserecoveries and sneaking down to wherever my group is waiting.<br>
<br>
Enkara Frostrose<br>
Level 57 Tarrew Marr Mine Detector <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udandaekofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dandaek of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 5:19:57 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lox204/face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Be careful though...</span><hr size=1> Holy god, this may well be the best update they've ever made. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.geocities.com/lox204/sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubraxana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Braxana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/00 6:36:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Spells do not break Hide!</span><hr size=1> This is amazing! I didn't realize the /con had been fixed sothat things that cannot see us are &quot;indifferent&quot;. That's GREAT!<br>
<br>
One thing I ~did~ notice was that they finallyfixed the bug whereby casting on a hidden rogue would make hervisible. They mentioned it in the patch message RE: bard songs,but I didn't have a bard nearby tonight (before they took theservers down again) but I had a druid cast on me while I wassneaking/hiding.... NO EFFECT! I was ~not~ made visible! Thisis GREAT!<br>
<br>
I'm so giddy with excitement and joy! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICONEND--> <br>
